included.summary:
Areas of expertise:
- Qualitative and Quantitative (mixed-methods) User Research
- UX Strategy and Facilitation 
- Information Architecture
- Development of Custom Interfaces

22 years work experience in diverse domains (software, aviation, education, biomedical, consumer/retail). I have worked as research lead in large product teams at Fortune 500 companies and have also been the UX team of one, developing an user experience practice from the ground-up in small businesses and non-profits. 

I think of my skills as being technology agnostic: I have worked on websites, mobile apps, kiosks, biomedical devices, and air-traffic displays. 

What keeps me enthused:  
- I really enjoy garnering relevant and insightful data about and from users to drive design solutions
- I like looking back on my work and being able to say I helped to design compelling products and services that enhanced people's lives.

Authors: Andrea CantÃº, Shobana Subramanian & Erika Noll Webb

Poster presented at UXPA 2013, July 2013, Washington DC

Abstract: The term digital natives has been in use to describe the generation of people who have always had the internet and technology. Although for the most part this population has not entered the workforce, their uses and expectations of technology are of interest to corporations. In this study, we surveyed 90 high school and college students about their uses of smart phones in order to understand their expectations about that technology. We discovered that even within this group of 13 to 24 year olds, differences between those in high school and those in college exist in a number of areas.
